    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nThis PR: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/26555 adds `linehl` highlight groups for highlighting whole line background in diagnostic.\r\n\r\nBut I noticed when I `Substitude` like `:%s/te`, `:'<,'>s/te`, the highlight group seems not show correctly.\r\n\r\nAn example:\r\n![image](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/39915562/6e3e0411-64ff-43ec-8b71-2092f727230e)\r\n\r\nAlso I noticed when using `:substitude`, the highlights like: `CursorLine`, `Visual`, will be disabled temperory.\r\nSo maybe the `linehl` should also be disabled temporary in subsitute mode?\r\n\r\nRelated PR: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/26555\r\ncc @gpanders @glepnir @wookayin \r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nMinimal reproduction config:\r\n```lua\r\nlocal lazypath = vim.fn.stdpath(\"data\") .. \"/lazy/lazy.nvim\"\r\nif not vim.loop.fs_stat(lazypath) then\r\n  vim.fn.system({\r\n    \"git\",\r\n    \"clone\",\r\n    \"--filter=blob:none\",\r\n    \"https://github.com/folke/lazy.nvim.git\",\r\n    \"--branch=stable\", -- latest stable release\r\n    lazypath,\r\n  })\r\nend\r\nvim.opt.rtp:prepend(lazypath)\r\nrequire(\"lazy\").setup({\r\n  {\r\n    \"neovim/nvim-lspconfig\",\r\n    config = function()\r\n      vim.opt.termguicolors = true\r\n      vim.api.nvim_set_hl(0, \"DiagnosticErrorLn\", { bg = \"#dc143c\" })\r\n      vim.api.nvim_set_hl(0, \"DiagnosticWarnLn\", { bg = \"#b8860b\" })\r\n      vim.api.nvim_set_hl(0, \"DiagnosticInfoLn\", { bg = \"#00afaf\" })\r\n      vim.api.nvim_set_hl(0, \"DiagnosticHintLn\", { bg = \"#00af00\" })\r\n      vim.api.nvim_set_hl(0, \"Search\", { bg = \"#00af00\", fg = \"#000000\" })\r\n\r\n      vim.diagnostic.config({\r\n        signs = {\r\n          linehl = { \"DiagnosticErrorLn\", \"DiagnosticWarnLn\", \"DiagnosticInfoLn\", \"DiagnosticHintLn\" },\r\n        },\r\n      })\r\n      require(\"mason\").setup()\r\n      require(\"mason-lspconfig\").setup({ ensure_installed = { \"lua_ls\" } })\r\n      require(\"lspconfig\").lua_ls.setup({})\r\n    end,\r\n  },\r\n  { \"williamboman/mason.nvim\" },\r\n  { \"williamboman/mason-lspconfig.nvim\" },\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nThe highlight of `Search` should applied properl in `subsitute` mode with `linehl` of diagnostic.\r\n\r\nOr temporary disable `linehl` of diagnostic in `subsitute` mode.\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-2296+gcca8a78ea\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nidk\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nUbuntu 20.04 in WSL2\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nWindows Terminal Preview 1.20\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\ntmux-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nbuild from repo",
